PLUM POINT ENERGY ASSOCIATES REACTIVE SUPPLY AND VOLTAGE CONTROL FROM GENERATION OR OTHER SOURCES SERVICE
Plum Point Energy Associates ("PPEA") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation or Other Sources Service ("Reactive Service") from an electric generation facility located near Osceola, Arkansas ("Facility") that is interconnected to the transmission system operated by the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. ("MISO"). This Reactive Service Tariff sets forth PPEA's revenue requirement for the provision of Reactive Service from PPEA's ownership share of the Facility (56.85%) pursuant to Schedule 2 of the MISO Open Access Transmission, Energy and Operating Reserve Markets Tariff.
Total charges for any 12-month period will not be less than the sum of the annual charges specified below.
REACTIVE SERVICE REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The total Reactive Service annual revenue requirement is $700,000 and the total Reactive Service monthly revenue requirement is $58,333.33.
